LIEUTENANT-GENERAL Nneke Ledwaba has received the Limpopo sword of command. The Limpopo police commissioner was handed the symbolic sword by acting national police commissioner, Kgomotso Phahlane.The handover took place at a ceremony held at the Seshego Stadium outside Polokwane, Limpopo. Top cops from Limpopo, who have served in the force for about 30 years, were also honoured with medals. Speaking at the event, Phahlane congratulated Ledwaba and reminded him of his responsibility to ensure the safety of Limpopo&rsquo;s people.&ldquo;Ever since you arrived in the province, you and your team have done well. We have noted commendable progress in the fight against crime,&rdquo; he said.Ledwaba said he was grateful that he was trusted with the sword. He promised to lead the provincial police with integrity and to continue fighting crime. He expressed appreciation for the leadership and guidance of former police minister Nathi Nhleko and his deputy, Maggie Sotyu. He welcomed new Police Minister Fikile Mbalula and his team.He urged cops to approach challenges with renewed enthusiasm in the new financial year, which he said had come with new leaders.&ldquo;We still need the community to work with us to defeat crime,&rdquo; said Ledwaba.